<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-30T00:50:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-30T00:50:00-05:00" n="116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.A Summaries/9–3049:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United
                                    Nations</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                            <dateline>
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-30T00:50:00-05:00">September
                                    30, 1949—12:50 a. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                            <p>1204.</p>
                            <p>. . . . . . .</p>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">General Assembly</hi> (230<hi rend="smallcaps">th Plenary</hi>)</p>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">summary</hi>
                            </p>
                            <p>By a vote of 45–6 (Yugoslavia, and Soviet bloc)–5 (Afghanistan,
                                Haiti, Israel, Syria, Yemen), the <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>
                                Sept. 29 approved the <gloss target="#t_GC1">GC</gloss>
                                recommendation for inclusion in the agenda and allocation to
                                Committee 1<note n="1" xml:id="d116fn1">The First (Political and
                                    Security) Committee of the General Assembly.</note> of the
                                Chinese charge that the USSR was threatening the <pb facs="0213" n="197" xml:id="pg_197"/> political independence and territorial
                                integrity of China and peace in the Far East.<note n="2" xml:id="d116fn2">See <hi rend="italic">Official Records</hi>,
                                    Plenary Meetings of the General Assembly, 20 September–10
                                    December 1949, p. 95.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>. . . . . . .</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>